data.name: hps.ToolTip
data.value: Higher frequency harmonics will appear at multiples of the device sampling rate's fundamental frequency. This is because it's still possible for higher sampling rates to have generated the observed data, albeit less likely. The Harmonic Product Spectrum algorithm attempts to eliminate these harmonics using displaced downsampled partials. Useful in situations where the fundamental frequency isn't obvious due to excessive noise.

data.name: lowCut.ToolTip
data.value: Cuts out frequencies below ~50 Hz, which usually represent the raised floor of the time domain histograms. It is recommended to leave this checked as devices typically operate at higher sampling rates. Uncheck only if analyzing a device with an extremely low sampling rate.

data.name: tbBinRate.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the rate at which to bin observed data for the time domain histograms. Higher values will group the data into smaller bins and thus be able to analyze higher device sampling rates. Increasing the value won't yield any additional precision for lower device sampling rates.
